# API Documentation Rules (OpenAPI/Swagger)
Description: Standards for documenting REST APIs using SpringDoc and Swagger UI.

## Configuration
- **Library**: `springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui` (v2.x for Boot 3).
- **Path**: Swagger UI at `/swagger-ui.html`, Docs at `/v3/api-docs`.

## Annotation Standards
- **Controller Level**: Use `@Tag` to group endpoints by domain (e.g., `Onboarding`, `Report`).
- **Method Level**:
  - `@Operation`: Summary and Description required.
  - `@ApiResponse`: Define response codes (200, 400, 404, 500).
- **DTO Level**:
  - `@Schema`: Describe fields, examples, and validation constraints.

## Example
```java
@Tag(name = "Onboarding", description = "User onboarding flow APIs")
@RestController
public class OnboardingController {

    @Operation(summary = "Start Onboarding", description = "Creates a new session")
    @ApiResponses(value = {
        @ApiResponse(responseCode = "200", description = "Session created"),
        @ApiResponse(responseCode = "400", description = "Invalid input")
    })
    @PostMapping("/start")
    public ResponseEntity<SessionResponse> start(@RequestBody @Valid StartRequest request) { ... }
}
```

## Enforcement
- All public APIs MUST have Swagger documentation.
- Do not expose internal/admin APIs without proper security grouping.
